The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, September 15, 2003 				 Delhi CAS talks agenda 
 A STAFF REPORTER																								The state government will send an official of the information and cultural affairs department for the conditional access system (CAS) talks on Monday, involving state representatives from the four metros and the Centre.																								Officials said on Sunday that three pleas would top the agenda: Dont implement CAS before all  doubts are cleared; Dont implement CAS till the festive  season is over in Bengal; Implement CAS simultaneously in  all four metros.																								We will have to be convinced that CAS is consumer-friendly, department principal secretary Basudeb Banerjee said on Sunday.
